    "client_msg_id": "eb5540cd-c9a3-4159-9f8d-1cd162541341",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "According to <https://mitpress.mit.edu/books/art-prolog-second-edition>, p. 19 (it's open access yay), it's a backward arrow for the (backward) logical implication. p. 120: \"The syntax of logic programs that we have been using fits within Standard Prolog except that we use some characters not available on a standard keyboard. We give the standard equivalent of our special characters. Thus :- should be used instead of ← in Prolog programs to separate the head of a clause from its body.\"\nI wonder why they didn't choose &lt;- as a symbol ...",
    "user": "U021MR7BK2Q",
    "ts": "1622250539.003900",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
