    "client_msg_id": "e107cd92-7541-4a2c-b087-ceb3d5b9548e",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Russell &amp; Norvig 2010, p. 339: \"Prolog programs are sets of definite clauses written in a notation somewhat different\nfrom standard first-order logic. [...] the clause is written “backwards” from what we are used to; instead of A ∧ B ⇒ C in\nProlog we have C :- A, B.\"",
    "user": "U021MR7BK2Q",
